a possible explanation is that the P heterogeneity at$\backslash$nmodal periods is greater than that inferred at ∼1s period. However,$\backslash$nsome mantle modes have nonnegligible sensitivity to vp and provide$\backslash$nevidence that the level of vp heterogeneity is the same at modal$\backslash$nperiods as it is at 1s, thus supporting, using an entirely different$\backslash$nkind of data, both the size and the pattern of lower mantle vp deduced$\backslash$nfrom travel times.},
